post_text:
ISD 601 Fosston Schools is participating in a USDA sponsored meal program that will allow us to serve free meals to enrolled students. This program is available until funding runs out or December 31, whichever comes first. Any enrolled student can participate, even if learning from home. If your child(ren) is distance learning (including high school students on the hybrid schedule) and you want to access free meals, please notify Melissa Kennedy at 218-435-6335.

Families should still fill out the free and reduced form; when funding for free meals is gone, we will return to charging for meals. This could happen at any time, and with very little notice. The free and reduced eligibility impacts our overall funding significantly. As well, our technology partner Garden Valley is offering a discount on internet servicesfor families that qualify for free or reduced priced meals.

Superintendent Sue Chase

post_text:
There have been some unforeseen delays in construction district wide in the past week. For the health and safety of students and staff, administration has elected to push back our official start of the school year. School will officially begin Thursday September 10, 2020. Regular classes will be held September 11.

Magelssen Elementary will hold its open house on Thursday, September 10, following the same appointment schedule sent out previously. Please bring your student(s) to the open house with you as this will be an attendance day.

7th Grade Orientation will be Wednesday, September 9, following the same schedule starting at 4:00 pm for the Maroon Group and 5:15 for the Grey Group.

Fosston High School will be in session on Thursday, September 10. The Grey Group will attend school on site on Thursday September 10 while the Maroon Group learns from home. Both groups will be learning from home on Friday, September 11.

IMPORTANT FACTS ON THE GRADUATION PARADE! PLEASE SHARE! On Saturday, June 13th, at 2:00 pm Fosston High School will be having a graduation parade. We ask that community members come out to show your support for our 2020 graduates. Graduates and their families will drive through town on the designated parade route (Map attached). The ceremony will be broadcast on KKCQ 96.7 FM and be live streamed on RJBroadcasting.com We ask spectators to station along the parade route, practice social distancing, and refrain from physical contact. Feel free to make signs to congratulate our graduates, cheer loudly, and show your Greyhound Pride. Thank you for helping to make this graduation a momentous occasion!

Sincerely,

Dominic Krump

Fosston High School Principal

Prizes this year were an Apple Ipad, and two pairs of Tozo Bluetooth Wireless Earbuds.

post_text:
Hello Senior Families,

This is Principal Krump with a Graduation Update.

The Caulfield photo for seniors on May 20th has been cancelled. We will be contacting families to schedule cap and gown pick up for June. When graduates pick up their caps and gowns, a photographer will be onsite to take pictures. It is our hope to have parents give diplomas to their child on material pick-up day. We will record this as part of the graduation video, and we will share the video with graduates and families. Graduation will be June 13th at 2:00 pm. Due to graduation guidelines set by the governor and Department of Education, we will be using the seniors' second choice, a parade-style graduation. Once our plan is finalized, we will share the date and times for material pick up, parade guidelines, and ceremony recordings. I thank families and graduates for their patience and understanding as we plan to give you the best possible graduation ceremony. Our ceremony may have changed, but the hopes, dreams, and well wishes for our graduates have not. Thank you!
text:
Hello Senior Families,

This is Principal Krump with a Graduation Update.

The Caulfield photo for seniors on May 20th has been cancelled. We will be contacting families to schedule cap and gown pick up for June. When graduates pick up their caps and gowns, a photographer will be onsite to take pictures. It is our hope to have parents give diplomas to their child on material pick-up day. We will record this as part of the graduation video, and we will share the video with graduates and families. Graduation will be June 13th at 2:00 pm. Due to graduation guidelines set by the governor and Department of Education, we will be using the seniors' second choice, a parade-style graduation. Once our plan is finalized, we will share the date and times for material pick up, parade guidelines, and ceremony recordings. I thank families and graduates for their patience and understanding as we plan to give you the best possible graduation ceremony. Our ceremony may have changed, but the hopes, dreams, and well wishes for our graduates have not. Thank you!

IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT HIGH SCHOOL TURN-IN DAY! Students are asked to turn in all school materials at the high school next Tuesday, May 12. The hours will be from 7:00 am to 5:30 pm. This will be a drive-through hand in. Please stay in your car, and we will meet you with instructions.

WHAT TO TURN IN: Your school computers, all textbooks, band instruments you have rented, school-owned calculators, and library books.

YOU WILL ALSO PICK UP YOUR YEARBOOK AT THIS TIME. There are a small number of extra books available for sale at $45 each on a first-come, first-serve basis, if you have not purchased one. If you have any questions about whether you ordered one, please contact Mrs. Mary Hanson at mhanson@fosston.k12.mn.us.

IN ADDITION, all student work needs to be turned in by May 12th.

Hello Magelssen Elementary Families:

I hope this message finds you well. The Magelssen Elementary staff has created distance learning packets for all students Pre-K through 6th grade. Packets will be available for pickup Friday, March 27th from 7:00am-5:30pm. Sorry, NO early pickups will be available. Original pick up date has been changed due to the governor‚Äôs ‚ÄúStay at Home Order.‚Äù Pickup procedure will be curbside on the south side of the elementary school (where students are typically picked up). Staff will be on hand to deliver packets to your vehicle. Please, remain in your vehicle and be patient. If you have any questions, please call Magelssen Elementary School @ 218-435-6036.

Dan Boushee-Principal

post_text: Congratulations to Faith Balstad, recipient of the Excel Award, sponsored by the Minnesota State High School League. She is one of 36 students in the state of Minnesota who was to be honored during half time of the girls AA championship game at Williams Arena in St. Paul on March 14th. VITAL Fosston
March 19 at 5:04 PM ¬∑

Calling all Greyhound Families!

We understand that these are uncertain times and that our children are feeling the stress. They‚Äôre missing their friends and the sense of community. We are determined to bring some light and fun to the situation.

VITAL is proud to present...Virtual Spirit Week!

This is a contest based on Facebook that is open to all students from Threeschool through 12th grade. Students who play along will be entered into drawings to win awesome prizes purchased here in town to support our local businesses.

Here‚Äôs how to play:

Each day, have your students dress up according to the theme. Snap a photo of your students and post it on Facebook - *MUST TAG @VITAL Fosston* on your post. That‚Äôs it!
** Earn an extra chance to win by liking the VITAL Facebook page and sharing this post! **

Winners will be announced on the VITAL Facebook page and in the Thirteen Towns.
Keep checking the VITAL Facebook page for more fun activities and contests while we are out of school.

Let‚Äôs show Covid-19 that it can‚Äôt keep the Greyhounds down! Ô∏è
